<P>
BERNARDI ATTENDS 1ST MEETING SINCE INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles City Councilman Ernani Bernardi returned to work Tuesday for the 
first time since being hospitalized for a cut to his head from a fall Jan. 4 at 
his Van Nuys home. 
</P>
<P>
"I feel fine," Bernardi, 77, said at his first council meeting since the 
Christmas recess. 
</P>
<P>
The northeast San Fernando Valley councilman had been suffering from a flu-like 
virus when he fell and struck his head on a kitchen cabinet, causing a cut that 
required five stitches to close. 
</P>
<P>
Bernardi, the council dean with 28 years of service, faces 12 challengers in 
the April 11 election in the 7th District, which includes Sylmar, Pacoima, 
Arleta and sections of Lake View Terrace, Mission Hills, North Hollywood, 
Panorama City, Sepulveda, Sun Valley and Van Nuys. 
