<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TRACTOR-TRAILER HITS MOVING VAN, BURNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The northbound Golden State Freeway south of Parker Road in Castaic was 
partially blocked for about four hours late Tuesday afternoon after a 
tractor-trailer rig hit a moving van parked on the shoulder of the road and 
burst into flames. 
</P>
<P>
George Spurgeon, 40, of Fontana, who was driving the tractor-trailer, let his 
rig "drift a little too far" to the right and struck the rear of the moving 
van, which had stopped because of brake problems, the California Highway Patrol 
said. Spurgeon's rig caught fire and came to rest in front of the moving van. 
</P>
<P>
Spurgeon suffered cuts on his head and right forearm. He was treated at Holy 
Cross Hospital in Mission Hills. The moving van did not catch fire and its 
driver was not injured, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
One to two lanes of the four-lane freeway were closed from 2 to 6 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
