<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Francis 53, St. John Bosco 50 -- Junior Forward Dominick Mumolo made a free 
throw with 5 seconds remaining and St. Francis added a meaningless basket at 
the buzzer in a Del Rey League game at St. John Bosco. 
</P>
<P>
The Golden Knights trailed by as many as 9 points with 4 minutes remaining in 
the final period but tied the score, 50-50, on a Jeff Dyrek jump shot with 50 
seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 63, Nordhoff 61 -- The Chargers, who led by as many as 23 in the second 
half, held on as Nordhoff fought back from a 53-33 deficit after 3 quarters in 
a Frontier League game at Nordhoff. Agoura forward Jeff Ingalls scored 20 
points and Gabe Bennett added 11. 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 77, Canyon 64 -- Trailing, 36-20, at halftime, Canyon narrowed the 
deficit to 10 points in the third quarter of the Golden League game but could 
draw no closer. 
</P>
<P>
Jamil Austin had 27 points, 10 rebounds and 5 assists for Canyon (10-6, 1-3), 
but his performance was offset by Palmdale's Shannon Culver, who scored 24 
points. Austin and Culver both made 8 of 17 field-goal attempts. Palmdale is 
3-1 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
Darren Oldenberg added 13 points for Canyon and Clint Beauer had 11 points and 
15 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Quartz Hill 79, Saugus 77 -- Saugus led by 8 points with 5 minutes remaining, 
but Quartz Hill went on a 12-0 run to pull out a Golden League win at Saugus. 
</P>
<P>
Senior forward Sean Legaux played his first game in 3 weeks and had 11 points 
for Saugus (1-13, 0-4). Teammate Aaron Volpe had a team-high 21 points. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep 74, Western Christian 61 -- Junior forward Jason Gerber scored 
22 points on 11-of-19 shooting and added 14 rebounds, 8 assists and 7 steals to 
lead the Mounties in an Alpha League game. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist 70, Maranatha 30 -- L. A. Baptist outscored Maranatha, 23-2, in 
the first quarter and was never threatened in an Alpha League game. Senior 
guard Dave Garcia scored 20 points and had 10 assists for L. A. Baptist (14-4, 
3-1). Forward Brett Craig added 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
Paraclete 88, Oakwood 75 -- Despite Mitchell Butler's game-high 35 points, the 
Gorillas (10-4) fell behind early in a nonleague game at Paraclete. 
</P>
<P>
Paraclete guard Jeff Zelenski made 4 of 5 3-point attempts and 10 of 10 free 
throws and finished with 32 points. 
</P>
<P>
Paraclete (14-1), ranked No. 7 in the Southern Section 2-A Division, made 28 of 
37 free throws. 
</P>
<P>
Grace Community 83, Highland Hall 59 -- Scott Lechuga scored 7 of his game-high 
27 points in the first quarter as Grace Community (9-3, 4-0) built a 30-7 lead 
and cruised to a Westside League win. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
