MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Stay tuned" has a new meaning to a 19-year-old late-night disc jockey in Iowa 
City, Iowa. When Daryl Berryhill stepped outside to get a snack from his car 
about 2:40 a.m. Monday, the station door locked behind him. The last song ended 
. . . followed by 45 minutes of silence. . . . Berryhill broke glass in a back 
door and pried open a security cage, but was unable to open a second set of 
doors leading to the studio. Deputy sheriffs finally arrived to assist in the 
re-entry. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
