<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Days of Lives" and "Knots Landing" were the winning shows in the the fifth 
annual Soap Opera Awards show presented in Los Angeles and televised nationally 
Monday on NBC. In the leading acting categories, winners included Joan van Ark 
of "Knots Landing," Jeanne Cooper of "The Young and the Restless," David Selby 
of "Falcon Crest" and Eric Braeden of "The Young and the Restless." The winners 
were selected through ballots sent to the 5 million readers of Soap Opera 
Digest magazine. ALEENE MacMINN 
