<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VIRGINIA WINS AS MORGAN TAKES OVER IN OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Richard Morgan scored the final 7 points of overtime Tuesday night to carry 
Virginia to a 64-58 Atlantic Coast Conference victory over Maryland at College 
Park, Md. 
</P>
<P>
Maryland (6-10 overall, 0-4 in the ACC) had a 58-57 lead when Morgan, who 
scored 21 points, sank a 3-point shot with 1:17 left. 
</P>
<P>
Morgan scored again with 17 seconds left and added 2 free throws with 3 seconds 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Blundin and John Crotty each scored 11 points for Virginia (9-6, 2-2). 
Tony Massenburg had 20 points for Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
Pittsburgh 73, Boston College 64 -- Bobby Martin scored 17 points and Jason 
Matthews added 16 as the Panthers downed the Eagles in a Big East game at 
Boston. 
</P>
<P>
Pitt (9-6, 2-2) pulled even, 55-55, with 5:51 left on Pat Cavanaugh's basket to 
start a 12-3 run. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Barros scored 15 points for Boston College (8-6, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 67, Southern Methodist 45 -- The Irish (8-2) scored the first 11 
points and held the Mustangs without a field goal for a 6-minute stretch in the 
first half at South Bend, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
Marquette 72, DePaul 64 -- Tyrone Baldwin scored 18 points, including 2 baskets 
in the final 5 minutes, as the Warriors got past the Blue Demons at Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
Baldwin's basket broke a 60-60 tie with 5:22 left and he gave Marquette (8-6) a 
68-64 lead by scoring with 55 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Stanley Brundy had 16 points for DePaul (10-8). 
</P>
</TEXT>
