<HEADLINE>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA GIRLS NO. 1 IN FIRST POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Brea-Olinda High School girls' basketball team holds the top spot in the 
first Orange County Sportswriters' Assn. poll of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Brea (13-2) has yet to lose to a county team this season. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View, which continues to rebound from an 8-16 record last season, is 
ranked second. The Seahawks, who have beaten Sunset League rival Fountain 
Valley twice this season, are 18-2. 
</P>
<P>
