<HEADLINE>
<P>
81 TRIBESMEN ARRESTED FOR BLOCKING LOGGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KUCHING, Malaysia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forestry officials have arrested 81 Malaysian tribesmen for setting up 
roadblocks to stop loggers from removing timber from their homesteads, 
officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The Penan tribesmen of Borneo Island, the region's last known tribe of nomadic 
hunters, were arrested in northern Sarawak state. The Penans, usually armed 
with blowpipes, have been protesting logging activities over the last two years 
in an effort to save their tropical rain forest homes. 
</P>
