</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Anaheim motorcyclist died instantly when he crashed into the back of a 
three-axle truck on the Garden Grove Freeway, a California Highway Patrol 
spokeswoman said today. Martin E. Henley, 28, was driving his 1978 Yamaha 
motorcycle at 85 to 90 m.p.h. eastbound near Harbor Boulevard at 8:25 p.m. 
Tuesday, when he passed two cars between lanes and slammed into the truck, CHP 
Officer Leslie Hill said. Henley was not wearing a helmet. No one else was 
injured. 
